b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48279.htm)  [Next](sbe48281.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n34\\. On account of taking and the declaration as to its moving about.\n\nThe text beginning 'And as a great king,' &c., declares that 'the Self taking\nthe pranas moves about in its own body,\n\np. 555\n\naccording to its pleasure' (B _ri_. Up. II, 1, 18), i.e. it teaches that the\nSelf is active in taking to itself the pra _n_ as and moving about in the\nbody.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 35. And on account of the designation of the Self as the agent in\nactions...](sbe48281.htm)\n\n"